snippet.title: Every Sister Ever | Ft. Tena Jaiin | The Paayal Jain
snippet.description:
Hey Guys
This video shows crazy side of sisters when they are around each other. We love and annoy each other at the same time. It is always Badi Behan vs Choti Behan but it is also Behan Behan ka pyaar. They fight for no reason, sometimes the elder sister wins and vice versa. First child always has to go through family restrictions whereas things are always easier for the younger one , like getting married the pressure of a good idle for younger sister .  Raksha Bandhan celebration with siblings . This is a very comic and relatable video.  Every Behen Shopping fancy rakhi, getting mehendi done girls Favourite Henna, buying new ethnic dress , trying on sharara, anarkali suits, baiting brother for gifts by being sweet, giving him trendy rakhis. Middle class rakshabandhan, school Rakhi celebration and so much more . Every sister ever can relate with this video .
This video is filled with such memories and situations we all have been in. 
Relish and Relive your Childhood Memories.. You will have major nostalgia
Do share it with your friends and family especially mom , sisters , brothers , cousins .. Comment down your Fav Part, 

Happy Raksha Bandhan 2024

snippet.title: Rakesh Barot | રાકેશ બારોટ | Reshma Thakor | રેશ્મા ઠાકોર | સોના રૂપનિ ભમ્મર વેલ | ગુજરાતી ગીત 2024
snippet.description:
સાંભળો રાકેશ બારોટ અને રેશ્મા ઠાકોરનું નવું  ગીત સોના રૂપાણી ભમ્મર વહેલ ફક્ત @SaregamaGujarati પર

Listen to Rakesh Barot and Reshma Thakor's new happy song "Sona Roopani Bhammar Vehl" only on @SaregamaGujarati 

Credits:
Singer: Rakesh Barot, Reshma Thakor 
Producer: Red Velvet Cinema 
Artist: Rakesh Barot, Sweat  sen , Divya Rajani ,kirtiy kashiya 
Concept: Savya Bhati , Bhavesh Gorsiya
Director: Bhavesh Gorasiya
Creative Head: Dhyey Films & Team
Technical Support: Jenish Talaviya
Production Manager: Ramesh Halol 
Lyrics: Chandu Raval
Music: Rakesh Barot, Mehul Barot
Dop: Anu Patel ( viral )
choreographer Dipak turi 
Editor: Anu Patel ( viral )
Makeup & Hair : chirag parmar, mandakini                            
Rakesh Barot Costume: Manisha R Barot
Recoding: Dhoon Digital Recoding Studio Adalaj
lokeshan Richiya gaam ( Halol )

Lyrics:
હે હાવ હોના ની હે એવી રૂપા ની
હે હાવ હોના રે રૂપા ની ભમ્મર વેલ
વેલડીએ ઘમકે છે જેણી ગુગર માણા રાજ
હે જોડો પરણિયા જોડો ભમ્મર વેલ
કોનુંડો આયો ને મૈયર જાવું માણા રાજ
હે ચાર પાંચ દાડા થી મને એ બધી ખબર છે
તારા રે પિયર સોમે તારી રે નજર છે
હે લોમી લોમી છે હે ઘણી છેટી
હે લોમી લોમી છે તારા મૈયરયા ની વાટ
ઘૂઘરા રે ધમકાવી વેલડું છોડું માણા રાજ
હે કોનુંડો આયો ને મૈયર જાવું માણા રાજ
હે વ્હલી મારી મૈયર જઇ ને તમે મોરે થઇ રમજો
મોરે થઈને રમશો તો અમને બહુ ગમશો
ઓ ભવો ભવ ભરથાર થઇ ને મળજો
તમારા પહેલા પિયુ મોત મને આવજો
ઓ પિયુ તમે બોલો વાત મા તહેવારે
નથી રોકી જતી પિયર જાત મને તહેવારે
હે હું ચંપો ને (૩) તમે છો મારી કેળ
કોનુંડો રમી ને રાજી રેજો મારા રાજ
કોનુંડો આયો ને મૈયર જાવું માણા  રાજ
હો આયો કોનુંડો પિયુ હૈયે હરખ છે હેંડો અવે મોડું રે થાય છે
હો તારું પિયર ને ગોડી મારું છે સાસરું
ચિંતા ના કરો વેલડું જશે રે પોચડું
હે મારી ગોથેનો ભેગી રે થઇ છે વટિયો મારી જોઈ બેઠી છે
હે ઉગિયો ઉગિયો રે (2)
હે ઉગિયો ઉગિયો રે, સોમે પિયેરે પ્રારભત
દાડો આથમતા પહોંચી જાસુ રે મારા રાજ
હે આવે કોનુંડો રમી રાજી થશુ મારા રાજ
હે આવે કોનુંડો રમી રાજી રેજો મારા રાજ

Let’s see what next 51days has in store for us 🥰 
No Plan, Japan! 🇯🇵

snippet.description:

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada

snippet.title: Kyu Bana Raksha Bandhan Sabse Special? 🥹
snippet.description:
Join us in this special Raksha Bandhan video as we celebrate the bond between siblings with our family! 🎉 From start to finish, the video is filled with love, laughter, and the deep connections that make family so special. From the early morning preparations to the Rakhi tying ceremony, every moment highlights the warmth and affection within our family.

Key highlights of the video include a special gift for our mother – a beautiful watch that perfectly matches her elegance. The fun shopping adventure with Poonam Bisht and Divya Bisht, where they carefully pick out gifts, adds a playful touch to the celebrations. The Rakhi ceremony itself is filled with nostalgic memories as all the siblings come together to relive their childhood moments.

Another memorable part of the day was the excitement of driving the new car, which everyone enjoyed together. The family also indulged in delicious biryani and samosas, adding to the festive atmosphere. The video also showcases Poonam Didi’s journey as a dedicated blogger, highlighting her hard work and the family’s support.

At the end of the video, Neetu Bisht  shares an intriguing detail, promising to reveal more in the next video. She mentions that she will talk about why her brother lives far away, what he does, and why he doesn’t visit them often. This revelation has left all the viewers eagerly awaiting the next video.

So, make sure to watch this video, like, share, and subscribe to stay connected with more heartwarming family moments! 🌟

--------------------------------------------------------
Popatlal is furious when the water stops mid-shower. He storms down and blames Bhide for the inconvenience. How will the society members react to Popatlal's outburst?

About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

Kaffara Episode 23 - [Eng Sub] - Ali Ansari - Laiba Khan - Zoya Nasir - 19th August 2024 - HAR PAL GEO

Sitara, a lively orphan living with her brother, aunt, and uncle, finds joy in life's small things despite her aunt's poor treatment. Her aunt keeps her around because she has a share in the family's property.
Salar, the son of a wealthy businessman, is passionate about photography, which often earns him criticism from his family. With a pure heart, Salar is known for evading his responsibilities.
At her cousin's wedding, Sitara wrongly assumes Salar is the photographer. Salar develops a soft spot for Sitara after seeing how poorly she is treated. However, due to a conspiracy, objections arise about their closeness. Salar, once again, avoids the issue, leaving Sitara to face doubts from her own family.

B Praak returns to Desi Melodies with the soul-stirring, "Mukke Paaye Si." It is a story featuring Sunny Kaushal and Neha Sharma of lost love along with the lingering pain it leaves behind, resonating with anyone who has felt the ache of a broken heart and reminding us of the strength required to endure a heartbreak. 

Listen to 'Mukke Paye Si' on your favourite streaming platform - https://umgindia.lnk.to/MPS

snippet.title: Mahindra Thar Roxx 2WD AX7L- ₹20.4 lakh | Real-life review
snippet.description:
Namaste friends, please LIKE & SUBSCRIBE :)

The Mahindra Thar Roxx is a five-door variant of the Thar SUV, launched by Mahindra & Mahindra in India on August 15, 2024. This model is designed to offer additional space and modern features while maintaining the off-road capabilities for which the Thar line-up is known. The Thar Roxx is built on Mahindra's new M_Glyde platform. It gets India’s First Crawl Smart Assist and IntelliTurn which can conquer tough terrains and tight turns with ease for superior off-road maneuverability. It also gets expansive Panoramic Skyroof which provides a wide open-air view, enhancing the sense of space in every drive. Also equipped with Harman Kardon 9-speaker system with QuantumLogic and Twin HD screens. #Mahindra #TharRoxx #MahindraTharRoxx

Petrol: 1997 cc, Inline-4 cylinder,  G20 mStallion engine with Turbo Petrol Direct Injection (TGDI), Automatic- 174 HP Power, 380 Nm Torque, Manual- 159 HP Power, 330 Nm Torque, Approx. 12 kmpl Average, 57 litre Fuel Tank, 6-speed Manual or 6-speed Aisin Torque Converter Automatic Transmission

Diesel: 2184 cc, Inline-4 cylinder, D22 mHawk engine with 1600 bar Common Rail Direct Injection Technology, RWD- 150 HP Power, 330 Nm Torque, 4WD- 172 HP Power, 370 Nm Torque, Approx. 15 kmpl Average, 57 litre Fuel Tank, 6-speed Manual or 6-speed Aisin Torque Converter Automatic Transmission

4 Variants: MX1, MX3, AX3L, MX5, AX5L, AX7L

2 Upholsteries: Black Fabric, Beige Leatherette

3 Wheels: 18 inch Steel, 18 inch Alloy, 19 inch Diamond Cut Alloy

7 Colours: Black, Blue, Grey, Brown, Red, White, Stealth Black

Price range (Excluding 4WD): Rs. 12.99 lakh - Rs. 20.49 lakh (Ex-showroom, Delhi)
